The paper deals with the task of assigning labels to an unlabeled data set using deep learning techniques. Specifically, it focuses on domain generalization and proposes a novel deep domain generalization architecture utilizing synthetic data generated by a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a protocol for applying DA methods to a DG scenario, which involves splitting the source data to training and validation parts, and treating the validation data as target data for DA. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of existing domain discrepancy metrics such as maximum mean discrepancy or correlation alignment, which suggests that it may belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image translation, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
